Environmental Toxicology and Pharmacology is a bimonthly peer-reviewed scientific journal covering research on the toxicological and pharmacological effects of environmental contaminants. It is published by Elsevier and was established in 1992 as the Environmental Toxicology and Pharmacology Section of the European Journal of Pharmacology, obtaining its current name in February 1996. The editors-in-chief are N. P. E. Vermeulen (Vrije Universiteit Amsterdam) and M. D. Coleman (Aston University). According to the Journal Citation Reports, the journal has a 2014 impact factor of 2.084. The Journal is included in the Index Medicus and in MEDLINE.
